name: Illumina HiSeq 2500
definition: The Illumina HiSeq 2500 is a sequencing machine developed by Illumina.

name: Illumina NextSeq 500
definition: The Illumina NextSeq 500 is a benchtop high-throughput sequencing machine developed by Illumina.

name: Illumina NovaSeq 6000
definition: The Illumina NovaSeq 6000 is a high-throughput sequencing machine developed by Illumina.

name: BGI MGISEQ-2000
definition: A next-generation sequencing (NGS) sequencer from Beijing Genomics Institute (BGI) based on DNA nanoball (DNB) and probe-anchor synthesis (cPAS) technology, which were also used in the previous version of the BGISEQ-500 device; however, the reagents for MGISEQ-2000 have been refined and the platform utilizes updated software.

name: PacBio Sequel II system
definition: The PacBio Sequel II system is a high-throughput, long-read sequencing machine developed by PacBio.

name: ONT PromethION
definition: The ONT PromethION is a high-throughput, high-sample number benchtop sequencing machine developed by Oxford Nanopore Technologies.

name: Not provided
definition: A categorical choice indicating that information of an expected format was not given; a value may be given at the later stage
